#load data and plot the data
monthly_data = read.csv("2013-2018MonthlyAverageData(2).csv")
x = seq(1,182, by =1)
plot(x,monthly_data$MonthlyAverage, xlab = "Months", ylab = "CO2 Level")

#preliminary trend estimation by eliminating the seasonal component of the data using a smoothing filter
season_pattern = season(monthly_data$MonthlyAverage,12)
only_trend = monthly_data$MonthlyAverage - season_pattern
plot(x,only_trend,type="o")

#eliminate the trend
m = trend(monthly_data$MonthlyAverage,2)
data_without_trend=monthly_data$MonthlyAverage-m
plot(x,data_without_trend, xlab = "Months", ylab = "CO2 Level removing trend",type="o" )

#Identify and remove seasonal pattern

monthsMean = seq_len(182)
seasonality = seq_len(12)

for (month in 1:12){
  currentMonths = seq(month,182,12)
  currentMonthsMean=mean(data_without_trend[currentMonths])
  monthsMean[currentMonths]=currentMonthsMean
  seasonality[month] = mean(data_without_trend)-currentMonthsMean
}
seasonality
##  [1] -0.7736502 -1.4757434 -2.8097318 -3.2397396 -2.3099667 -0.4670797
##  [7]  1.8075880  3.4087032  3.3869325  2.0749425  0.7887333 -0.2410285
plot(seq_len(12),seasonality,type="o")

plot(x,monthsMean,type="o")

#re-estimate the trend by substracting the season component.
#s stands for seasonal component.
#s stands for seasonal pattern
data_without_season=monthly_data$MonthlyAverage-monthsMean
plot(x,data_without_season,type="o")

#fit a model for the trend pattern
thetrend = lm(m~x+I(x^2))
summary(thetrend)

#Re-estimate and remove trend and seasonality, to get the stationary process and residual
#m stands for the new trend
m_new = trend(data_without_season,2)
data_without_season_and_trend = monthly_data$MonthlyAverage-monthsMean-m_new

plot(x,data_without_season_and_trend,type="o")

#Fitting an ARMA model

armafit = auto.arima(data_without_season_and_trend)
armafit

mt = 375.3 + 0.14*t + 0.0002143t^2 #st = -0.2029507 -0.7868745 -1.4965193 -2.8190324 -3.2491169 -2.3194395 -0.4766669 1.7978676 3.3988308 3.3768891 2.0647094 0.7782916 #Yt: phi_1 = 0.5390, phi_2 = 0.1545, sigma = 0.09051 library(“forecast”) the_forecast95 = forecast(armafit, h=1, level = c(95)) the_forecast95 the_forecast99 = forecast(armafit, h=1, level = c(99)) the_forecast99


#Adding on the trend and seasonal component. Final prediction
m_183 = 375.3 + 0.14*183 + 0.0002143*183^2
s_183 = -2.8190324
PE95 = -0.2066007 + m_183+ s_183 
upp95 = 0.3830663 + m_183+ s_183
